        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 18 at 4:54PM CDT until August 18 at 5:30PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Barrington to Hoffman Estates to near Bartlett to
near Dupage Airport, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

These severe storms will be near...
Barrington, Inverness, Mount Prospect, Wood Dale, Bloomingdale,
Glen Ellyn, Schaumburg, Elk Grove Village, Winfield, and Itasca
around 500 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of these severe thunderstorms include
Buffalo Grove, Wheeling, Prospect Heights, Des Plaines, Chicago,
Lombard, Bensenville, Glenview, Rosemont, Ohare Airport, Park Ridge,
Villa Park, Elmhurst, Northbrook, Northlake, Franklin Park, Schiller
Park, Niles, Bellwood, River Grove, Hillside, Melrose Park, Broadview
and Maywood.
</description>
        <instruction>A tornado watch remains in effect for the warned area. Tornadoes can
develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Although a tornado is not
immediately likely, if one is spotted act quickly and move to a place
of safety inside a sturdy structure, such as a basement or small
interior room.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
